By Deji Elumoye The new Chairman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), Abdulrasheed Bawa, is at the moment meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari at the State House, Abuja. <img src="https://i0.wp.com/storage.googleapis.com/thisday-846548948316-wp-data/wp-media/eada0aec-fb_img_1614262440570.jpg?w=696&#038;ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" />
Bawa, whose appointment as EFCC Chairman was confirmed by the Senate on Wednesday, is at the Villa to meet with the President as he begins his five-year tenure as head of the anti-graft agency. <img src="https://i0.wp.com/storage.googleapis.com/thisday-846548948316-wp-data/wp-media/ba42b4cb-fb_img_1614262429524.jpg?w=696&#038;ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" />The meeting is holding behind closed doors at the President’s office. Details later…